This paper discusses security and privacy attacks against machine learning models, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes new techniques for backdoor attacks against ML models, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also evaluates its techniques on image datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of generative networks in the proposed techniques could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of current defense mechanisms against backdoor attacks, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
